From Noah Ebije, Kaduna A Chieftain of People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in Kog State, Alhaji Abubakar Ibrahim Idris has congratulated Senator Ademola Adeleke on his election as the Governor-elect of Osun State. Adeleke of PDP defeated incumbent governor Oyetola Gboyega of the All Progressive Congress (APC) in the keenly contested election. “Your election was never a thing to doubt. You had the people of Osun State by your side. You fought to ensure your mandate was not stolen. You fought the good fight and held on to your victory to the very end of the process. “On behalf of my family, my support group, and myself, I celebrate you,” the congratulatory message from Alhaji Abubakar Ibrahim’s Media office, read. Alhaji Abubakar charged Senator Adeleke to continue the good works he is doing for the people of Osun State now that he is their Governor-elect. He wishes Senator Ademola Adeleke a successful tenure ahead.